Reporter
432 U.S. 63 *; 97 S. Ct. 2264 **; 53 L. Ed. 2d 113 ***; 1977 U.S. LEXIS 115 ****; 14 Fair Empl. Prac. Cas. (BNA) 1697; 14 Empl. Prac. Dec. (CCH) P7620TRANS WORLD AIRLINES, INC. v. HARDISON ET AL.
Prior History:  [****1]  CERTIORARI TO THE UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE EIGHTH CIRCUIT 
Disposition: The court reversed the judgment of the appeals court and found no violation of the civil rights laws because appellant had tried in a variety of ways to accommodate respondent employee, whose religious beliefs prohibited him from working on Saturdays. 
Case Summary




Procedural Posture
Appellant employer challenged reversal of a judgment from the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit, holding appellant had not satisfied its duty to accommodate and had committed an unlawful employment practice under § 703(a)(1) of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C.S. § 2000e-2(a)(1).
Overview
Appellant was an airline that operated a large maintenance and overhaul base. Respondent was an employee of appellant's who was prohibited from working on Saturday due to religious tenets. Appellant would not or could not accommodate respondent's need to be off on Saturday. Thereafter, respondent filed a discrimination action the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C.S. § 2000e-2(a)(1). Reversing the appeals court, which found appellant violated the Act, the court held that appellant did not violate the Act. In fact, the court noted that appellant tried to accommodate respondent by meeting with him to discuss alternatives, attempting to find someone to swap shifts with respondent, and attempting to find respondent another job. It was the union, not the employer, that was more unyielding. The court concluded that there was not even a suggestion of discriminatory intent in this case.
Outcome
The court reversed the judgment of the appeals court and found no violation of the civil rights laws because appellant had tried in a variety of ways to accommodate respondent employee, whose religious beliefs prohibited him from working on Saturdays.
